  <p>
    DevWire Times is an independent engineering publication for teams that need signal over noise.
    We translate platform changes, architecture decisions, and delivery patterns into practical reporting.
  </p>

  <h2>Our Reporting Lens</h2>
  <p>
    Our newsroom covers AI/ML systems, cloud and DevOps, software architecture, security, and engineering leadership.
    Every story is written for teams making weekly roadmap and operations decisions.
  </p>

  <h2>Editorial Methodology</h2>
  <p>
    We synthesize engineering blogs, release notes, technical incident writeups, and public benchmarks.
    We then frame the tradeoffs, business implications, and implementation guidance in concise briefings.
  </p>

  <h2>Who Reads DevWire</h2>
  <p>
    DevWire is read by founders, product leaders, staff engineers, SRE teams, and engineering managers at fast-moving software companies.
    If your team values factual reporting and actionable analysis, this publication is built for you.
  </p>
